data.description: This charming 50’s Victory bungalow is ready for its THIRD owner! The low maintenance brick exterior and newer concrete stoop gives a warm welcome to visitors. Original hardwood floors gleam all throughout! The large picture window in the front living room brings in a ton of natural light in the afternoon/evening. The oversized kitchen has plenty of seating around the table, as well as plenty of cabinetry and newer stainless-steel appliances! Don’t miss the three-season porch; perfect spot to enjoy your morning coffee! Your third bedroom upstairs has knotty pine with plenty of headroom. In your basement, don’t miss the equity building potential next to the wet bar and storage spaces! Your newer furnace and AC are ready for Minnesota and all its seasons! In the backyard alleyway is your newer remodeled garage. The Victory Memorial Parkway connects you to The Mighty Mississippi, Shingle Creek, and Theodore Wirth Regional Park. Don’t miss out!
